description: The myth of Paris as it took shape in nineteenth-century art and literature. Works by writers such as Hugo, Balzac, Baudelaire, and Rimbaud and by artists such as Delacroix, Gavarni, and Manet, as well as major impressionists such as Monet, Sisley, and Caillebotte. Other topics include nineteenth-century French history, Haussmann's urbanism, architecture, and the birth of photography.
title: CANCELLED
long_title: Paris, Capital of the Nineteenth Century
